<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1731,1982]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,285,1731,1757]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[294,609,1732,1757]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Nepalomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reunionensis">
<emphasis box="[294,609,1732,1757]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Nepalomyia reunionensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is close to 
<taxonomicName box="[753,884,1732,1757]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Nepalomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kotrbae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[753,884,1732,1757]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">N. kotrbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[893,963,1732,1758]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, differing in simple fore tarsus and in hypopygium morphology. The new species is related to the 
<emphasis box="[904,1014,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">pallipes-</emphasis>
species group (
<bibRefCitation author="Wang" box="[1202,1423,1769,1795]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Wang, M. Q., Yang, D. &amp; Grootaert, P. (2007) Revision of the Nepalomyia pallipilosa species group (Diptera, Dolichopodidae, Peloropeodinae). Biologia, 62 (6), 731 - 741." type="journal article" year="2007">
Wang et al. 
<number box="[1356,1423,1769,1795]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), differing from Oriental species in bearing posterodorsal row of 
<number box="[895,934,1806,1832]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5-6</number>
dark setae on hind tibia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
